@NODE Introduction
@{APEN 3}@{B}Introduction @{ub}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Alien Fish Finger is a little platform game set on an Alien world 
with you in control of some hero type dude called Frank Finger on a 
mission to save Earth from the deadly clutch of the evil Aliens.
You are armed with an upgradeable weapon, which comes complete with 
a deadly powerful Grenade launcher.


@{APEN 3}@{b}System Requirements@{ub}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{b}Minimum:@{ub}
An Amiga with 1 meg chip RAM.
A500+, A600  etc.

@{b}Recommended:@{ub}
A1200 or above, for extra sound FX

@ENDNODE


@NODE Story
@{APEN 3}@{B}THE STORY@{ub}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~
Death, destruction, pain, misery.  What was once a bright, beautiful 
planet is now blackened by the consent invasion of death making Alien 
bombers.  Planet 'Earth' as it is today. Thousands, if not millions 
of innocent lives wiped out with the consent attacks of the war of 
the Aliens.

There is only one force of resistance who are known as the freedom 
fighters, an Earth based force of defence, now crippled with the 
heavy firepower of the fearsome Alien enemy.  There stands one man, 
just as fearsome and brave, his name;... `Frank Finger`.   One of 
the last of his kind to survive the terror, a fighter for freedom 
and victory.  
He and the others are all sickened of the sight of the aliens near 
winning the war.  They prepare to launch one final attack, the final 
chance of survival.  If they don't succeed the Earth is doomed.  
`Finger` gathers his men.  He stands tall, pauses, and looks at all of 
his comrades, before saying, "They've killed our families, they've 
destroyed our world, OUR HOME!.  Now we take their war to them, 
THEIR WORLD, THEIR HOME!  
NOW WE FIGHT FOR FREEDOM!" . . . . . .


@ENDNODE

@NODE "PLAYING THE GAME"
@{APEN 3}@{B}PLAYING THE GAME@{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You play the role of 'Frank Finger'.  You will be given the task 
of completing a series of missions on the alien planet surface.  Your 
only guide is from Head-Quarters, in touch with them by micro-radio.  
They will brief you on your mission and progress.

On successfully completing a mission, return back to your Space-Ship.  
To take off, jump into the cockpit and sit down. The door should 
close, and the Ship should take off.

The status bar, at the top of the screen, display the following 
things:

@{APEN 3}@{B}Energy Meter: @{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You are given 5 energy squares for each life. Every time you get hit 
by enemy fire or fall to far, you will lose one.  When you have lost 
all 5 you will loose a life.  More energy can be picked up from alien 
dead bodies.

@{APEN 3}@{B}Grenades: @{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~
On starting a game, you are granted 5 Grenades.  These are used for 
throwing at aliens.  If timed right you can kill multiple aliens with 
one throw.  They can be thrown against certain walls to destroy them. 
Be careful as they can also harm you.  More can be picked up from 
dead alien bodies.

@{APEN 3}@{B}Weapon Gauge: @{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Upon starting a game, you are given a low powered basic weapon.  Each 
time you kill an alien and then pick up his gun, the gauge is 
increased by one notch. When you have successfully collected enough 
guns you will upgrade to the next more powerful weapon.  
To upgrade to the very last weapon in the game (The Trophy Gun), you 
will have to collect almost every single alien gun to stand any chance 
of gaining it.  This includes guns in secret bonus rooms as well.

@{APEN 3}@{B}Spell Extra: @{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Pick up letters from dead alien bodies, and spell the word EXTRA for 
(you guessed it) an extra man.

@{APEN 3}@{B}Men: @{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~
The number of men displayed on the title bar represents the number of 
lives you currently have.  The more men you have the better change 
you have of survival.

@{APEN 3}@{B}Gravity Reducer Device (G.R.D.)@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
In Frank Fingers backpack contains a G.R.D.  This device allows Frank to 
jump that little bit higher then normal when you hold jump that little 
bit longer.  This device also allows Frank to change direction in mid air, 
defying all laws of physics.


@{APEN 3}@{B}Controls:@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~
@{b}Joystick: @{ub}
  * Use @{b}LEFT@{ub}/@{b}RIGHT@{ub} to move (you guessed it) left or right.
  * @{b}UP@{ub} or @{b}2ND FIRE@{ub} button (if set in the config options) to jump.
  * @{b}DOWN@{ub} to Duck.
  * @{b}DOWN@{ub} and @{b}LEFT@{ub}/@{b}RIGHT@{ub} to lower gun to the floor.
  * @{b}FIRE@{ub} button to fire Weapon.
  * Hold down @{b}FIRE@{ub} button for half a second to throw a Grenade.
    - Running then throwing grenade, extends its distance (New).
    - @{b}DOWN@{ub} + Grenade rolls grenade at a slow speed. Less bouncing. 
      Used for rolling down stairs or off cliff with enemies below (New).
      Care should be taken not to kill yourself with this one as the range
      is short.
    - @{b}DOWN@{ub} + @{b}LEFT@{ub}/@{b}RIGHT@{ub} + Grenade, same as above, but with greater 
      distance and speed (New).

  Esc key to Quit.
  P key to Pause



-------
Every time you lose a life, your dead body will remain in the game. 
Every time you play a new game of 'AFF' you will see where you 
died. The bodies will also be saved to disk along with your high 
scores and achievements.  These can be cleared with options in the main 
title screen.



@{B}NTSC and Widescreen TV`s now supported!!

NTSC screen mode@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Use the new screen configuration menu to adjust the top border and height
of the screen.  Move joystick up and down to move screen up and down. 
Move joystick left and right to adjust the height.  The maximum height 
allowed is 256 pixels high.  Position the bar at the bottom of the screen 
so you CAN see the yellow part, but NOT the blue part.  It`s important you 
get these setting correct as the game use`s these variables to scroll the
screen up and down in line with the main character.
Once happy, you can press `S` key to save settings to disk, then joystick 
fire button or Esc key to Exit.

@{B}Widescreen TVs@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
To setup a wide screen TV, basically it`s the same as setting up a NTSC 
screen, but you need to do one step first and that is to configure your 
Widescreen TV to Zoom mode (the mode where the top and bottom of a 4:3 
screen is cut off and not stretched).

@{B}Difficulty Settings@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Points given on entering a new screen: 
		   350 points on Easy 
		   500 points on Medium
		   750 points on Hard mode
		   
@{B}Extra Sound FX :D@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
A1200 owners are treated with extra sound effects as standard.  :)
If you have an A500+ or an A600 with MORE then the standard 1 Meg chip memory, 
then while loading the game, hold down the joystick fire button and you too 
can have the full sound FX`s.  
Sorry for this extra step, but I could not find any commands in my programming 
language to tell me how much memory the Amiga the game is running on has.  
Answers on a post card. :p.   


@{b}More@{ub}
~~~~
As said above I`ve added many new sound effects to the game, but there 
can be even more if you so wish to add.  If you were to make these yourself 
then you can also have sounds for each of the Letter pick-ups, and also the 
health pickup too.  File names to use are below.  The files need to be in .iff 
format.   Due to lack of disc space (plus maybe a lack of talent), I thought I 
would leave these for you, the Community, to make. 

AFF-E-FX.iff  
AFF-X-FX.iff
AFF-T-FX.iff
AFF-R-FX.iff
AFF-A-FX.iff
AFF-HealthFX.iff
AFF-DieFX4.iff <an extra enemy death sound too.

Just drop the files into the main game folder.  As long as they are spelt 
correctly and the Amiga has more then 1 Meg chip memory the game should load 
and use them.

If you have a sound pack, or a Mod to the original sounds, that you wish to 
release, please distribute these separately to the main game.  Include 
instructions on how to install plus how to un-install, plus a link to my 
charity page would be nice too.

Thank you

	  
_________________________________________________________________
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ACHIEVEMENTS PAGE"
@{APEN 3}@{B}ACHIEVEMENTS PAGE@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
I got this idea from playing Steam games on the PC.  Basically, you 
receive trophies for completing tasks in the game. Example: get 
trophies each for completing the game in Easy, Medium, and Hard mode. 
Find trophies in the secret hidden areas; get a big trophy for finding 
them all. 
Some trophies should be easy to get but the "Finish the game without 
losing a life" trophy should challenge any `Alien Fish Finger` veteran. 

Just to make things clear:-
The "Finish the Game" achievements, you must start the game from level 1.  
Starting from level 4 will not grant you the trophies.

To earn the "Complete the game with only basic Fire weapons" achievement, 
you must finish the game with the 1st or the 2nd gun upgrade.  Once you 
have upgraded to the 2nd gun upgrade, do not collect any more guns.   
However you CAN use Grenades if you so wish.

Finding trophies in secret rooms after starting from Level 4 is allowed.
Trophies that have been found already in secret rooms will appear grey. 

My tip would be to play game on Easy mode for some of the harder
achievements.

No prize from me for completing them all, but well done if you do.

_________________________________________________________________
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tips"
@{APEN 3}@{B}General Tips@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Some levels require you to complete a mission before you can go on to 
the next, so read each mission briefing carefully before starting.

Take your time when running around. Steep drops can deplete your 
energy, so take your time when running down hills or jumping from 
cliffs.

Use grenades whenever possible as there are plenty to go around.  
Grenades can be bounced of walls, so getting the angle right could 
kill some aliens out of reach of your normal line of fire. By runing 
and then throwing a grenade will extend the distance it can be 
thrown.

Search out the levels for secret rooms. Some are easily found while 
some are not. They contain lots of goodies from energy to extra men.

Try not to miss many guns because as the game gets harder, you will 
need the best weapon for survival.


@endnode

@NODE History
@{APEN 3}@{B}History@{APEN 1}@{UB}

V1.00  1995      * First release, after 14 months in development.

V1.20  1995-1997 * Added many extra sound FX.
	         * Changed colour palette on some screens.  
                 * Minor level tweaks
                 * Changed some text here and there.

V1.30  2010-2011 * Unfroze game from cryogenics.  Removed mothballs.
                 * Changed licence from Shareware to @{"Charity ware" link "Copyright"}
                 * Added more sound FX (still no music sorry)
                 * Added to the game an Achievements page.
                 * Added 2nd fire button option for jump. Option is 
                   saved to disk so never have to change it again.
                 * Added menu option for Grenade.  Now you can choose
                   whether to throw a Grenade by holding fire button,
                   or throw it by releasing the fire button.  
                   Option also saved to disk.
       	         * Added a start from Level 4 option.
       	         * Added 4 extra secret hidden areas, 
       	           one on Level 1,
       	           one on Level 5, 
       	           and 
       	           two on Level 6. 
       	           (who will be the first to find them?).
       	         * Added new screen on Level 4.
       	         * Added Stencil/Masking to all maps.  This allows 
       	           player and enemies to appear behind foreground 
       	           objects such as fences and trees.  This has 
       	           created a sense of 'depth' to the maps.
       	         * New Trigger routine for enemy entrances.  Before 
       	           enemies would enter the screen after a set number
       	           of seconds.  Now the game has been programmed to 
       	           also allow enemies to enter screen if player moves
       	           to an invisible trigger zone instead of waiting a
       	           set number of time.  The trigger zone can be as 
       	           large or as small as I like.  This has gave me 
       	           more freedom to place enemies in relation to where 
       	           the player is.  A combination of both Trigger and 
       	           Time can be used too.  All for better game play.
       	         * New weapon - Rock Gun.
       	         * Added rain to some of the outside levels.
       	         * MORE BLOOD!  ALIEN Fish Finger had blood, but now 
       	           it has more.  Added an extra blood routine to 
       	           skater blood from shot enemies and player.  Added 
       	           Low, Medium and High options in config menu.  
       	           Option is also saved to disk.
		 * Easy, Medium & Hard modes added.  Option also saved 
		   to disk.  Points given on entering a new screen: 
		   350 points on Easy 
		   500 points on Medium
		   750 points on Hard mode
       	         * Changed some things with big boss enemies.
       	         * Cropping Enemies off the edge of the screen.  If a 
       	           player leaves a screen full of enemies then re-enters
       	           the same screen, then the game now makes sure no 
       	           enemy is within 50 pixels of the player.  
       	           This should hopefully reduce player from getting 
       	           swamped before even getting a chance to shoot.
       	         * Made many many small level tweaks.
       	         * Enemy dead bodies now remain on the screen when you
       	           walk off that screen then back on.
       	         * Now that most people have hard drives, flash drives,
       	           or emulators; 200 player dead body positions now get 
       	           saved to disk.  Before was only 20.
       	         * Fixed bug where bonus items disappear while still 
       	           bouncing if player leaves the screen then re-enters.
       	         * Destructible objects now crumble and fall to the 
       	           ground in small pieces when shot.
       	         * The game now remembers more bullet holes (even more
       	           if playing on a A1200 or above).   This was done more
       	           so for the level 2 UFO Boss.  The bit where you have
       	           to shoot through a pile of rocks.  If the player goes
       	           for a walk around the map, the shot out holes should
       	           still be there saving the player from having to shoot
       	           through them again.  
       	         * Game remembers grenade holes now too.
       	         * Added water droplets dripping from cave Stalactites.
       	         * Added Jet engine flames to players Drop Ship.
		 * Added NTSC support for our American and Canadian friends. 
		   I've combined this with a new screen configuration menu.
		   There will now be no problems of the top or bottom of 
		   the screen being cut off during game play.  
       	         * Widescreen TV's supported.  Use the above options to 
       	           configure your widescreen TV.
       	 
       	         2010-2011 updates were all done using an Amiga emulator 
       	         on a PC.  No real Amiga was touched (or harmed) in the 
       	         making.  Thanks again to WinUAE and it's makers.
       	         
       	                                  \\(^.^)/
       	          


@endnode

