@NODE KnownBugs
@{APEN 3}@{B}Known Bugs@{UB}@{APEN 1}

Sound problems
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
On some hi-spec Amiga's there could be problems with the sound. IF 
you get crackly sounds, then disabling CPU caches before running the 
game should hopefully fix the issue.

RTG problem
~~~~~~~~~~~
game may have problems running on an Amiga that uses a RTG graphics
card.  Sometimes the game jumps to Workbench screen while loading 
in new level data, but then is unable to return back to the game.  
You can hear the game playing in the background but you are unable 
to see it.  This only happens sometimes, not always.
The solution is to run game on a standard Amiga Workbench or from 
floppy.  If you do use a RTG card and you find yourself looking at 
a workbench screen instead of the game then I'm sorry.


_________________________________________________________________
@ENDNODE



